## System-Specific Conventions

### Scene Commands

Use these commands to trigger system capabilities:

| Command | When to Use |
|---------|-------------|
| `/new-project` | Starting a brand new project |
| `/feature` | Adding a feature to existing project |
| `/bugfix` | Fixing a bug |
| `/refactor` | Code refactoring |
| `/design` | UI/UX design work |
| `/review` | Comprehensive code review (5-layer) |
| `/hunt` | Security vulnerability hunting |
| `/analyze` | Competitor analysis with OpenDigger |
| `/loop` | Long-running autonomous iteration |
| `/simplify` | Code simplification (clarity over cleverness) |
| `/optimize` | Performance optimization (measure-first) |
| `/polish` | Frontend UI polish with DaisyUI/Animate.css/Lucide |

### Memory System

Four memory tools are available:
- **Claude-Mem** — Markdown-based persistent memory (native plugin, no prefix)
- `memory-agentmemory_*` — SQLite structured data
- `memory-nexo_*` — Graph-based semantic memory
- `memory-codegraph_*` — Code relationship knowledge graph

Always use the correct prefix for prefixed tools. Never mix prefixes.

### Review Pipeline

5-layer review runs automatically:
1. ESLint + reviewdog (syntax, style, common bugs)
2. react-doctor (React-specific patterns)
3. Playwright (visual regression)
4. Claude Code Headless (semantic logic, security)
5. Aggregate (prioritize, deduplicate)

Layer 1-2 auto-fix. Layer 3-4 require manual review.

